Mystic Quizmaster – Privacy Policy and Terms & Conditions
This document contains both the Privacy Policy and the Terms and Conditions for the mobile game “Mystic Quizmaster” (“the Game”, “we”, “our”, “us”).

By installing and playing Mystic Quizmaster, you agree to these Terms and this Privacy Policy.

1. Data Controller

The data controller in the sense of applicable data protection laws (such as the EU General Data Protection Regulation – GDPR) is:

OaktwonRuinStudio
Email: Oaktownruinstudio@gmail.com

This contact can be used for all questions regarding privacy and data protection in relation to Mystic Quizmaster.

2. Privacy Policy
2.1. What data we collect
2.1.1. Data stored locally on your device

The Game stores only the minimum data necessary for gameplay, for example:

current level and game progress,

unlocked cards and in-game achievements,

in-game settings (such as sound preferences).

This information is stored only on your device, using the standard storage mechanisms of the Android operating system (e.g. SharedPreferences and similar).

We do not operate our own backend servers for this Game and we do not have automatic remote access to this data. The data is not transmitted to us unless you consciously send it to us (for example by sending a screenshot or log file in an email).

You can delete this data at any time by uninstalling the Game or, where available, by using in-game reset options.

2.1.2. No user account and no login

Mystic Quizmaster does not require registration and does not create any user account.
We do not collect names, email addresses, passwords or other contact details from players through the Game.

2.1.3. No analytics, no online tracking

The current version of the Game:

does not integrate third-party analytics SDKs (such as Google Analytics for Firebase),

does not use online tracking,

does not use cookies or similar tracking technologies.

2.1.4. No advertising networks (production use)

Within the Game there is only a test dialog that simulates a rewarded ad (“Watch Ad” test screen). This dialog is purely simulated and does not contact any advertising server.

The Game currently does not integrate real advertising SDKs and does not display production ads from ad networks.

If we decide to integrate real ads or analytics in the future, this Privacy Policy will be updated before such changes go live.

2.1.5. Data collected by app stores and platforms

When you download Mystic Quizmaster from an app store (for example Google Play), the operator of that platform may collect and process personal data independently from us (e.g. your Google account, device information, purchase history).

This processing is governed exclusively by the privacy policy of the respective platform.

We do not control and are not responsible for this platform-level data processing.

2.2. Legal bases (GDPR)

Where the GDPR applies, we rely on the following legal bases:

Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR – processing necessary for the performance of a contract
(providing the Game and saving your progress locally on your device).

Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR – legitimate interests
(improving the Game, defending against misuse). Since we do not collect analytics or server logs for ordinary gameplay, this basis is mainly relevant if you contact us directly (e.g. support emails).

If you contact us by email or other channels, we process the data you provide (e.g. email address, content of the message) solely to handle your request. The legal basis is Art. 6(1)(b) and/or Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR.

2.3. Children’s privacy

Mystic Quizmaster is not specifically targeted at children, but it also does not contain realistic violence, sexual content, or gambling.

We do not knowingly collect personal data from children. Because the Game does not require registration and does not send gameplay data to our servers, we normally cannot identify users as children.

If you are a parent or guardian and believe that we have collected personal data about your child, please contact us using the details above. We will review the request and take appropriate action.

2.4. Data recipients and international transfers

Because the Game stores progress only locally and does not communicate with our own servers, there are no regular recipients of personal data for ordinary gameplay.

If you contact us (e.g. by email), your correspondence is processed by our email provider and, where applicable, by service providers we use to organise support (e.g. helpdesk tools, cloud storage). These providers may be located in the EU or in other countries.

Where data is transferred to countries outside the EU/EEA, we take reasonable steps to ensure an adequate level of data protection (for example by using the EU Standard Contractual Clauses, where applicable).

2.5. Your rights under the GDPR

If the GDPR applies to you, you have the following rights regarding your personal data:

right of access (Art. 15 GDPR),

right to rectification (Art. 16 GDPR),

right to erasure (Art. 17 GDPR),

right to restriction of processing (Art. 18 GDPR),

right to data portability (Art. 20 GDPR),

right to object (Art. 21 GDPR).

Because the Game itself does not transmit gameplay data to us, these rights mainly apply to data that arises through direct communication with us (e.g. support emails).

To exercise these rights, please contact us using the details provided in section 1.

You also have the right to lodge a complaint with a data protection supervisory authority, in particular in the EU member state of your habitual residence, place of work, or the place of the alleged infringement.

2.6. Data retention

Local game data on your device:
Stored until you uninstall the Game, reset the app data, or use in-game reset options. We cannot access or delete this data remotely.

Support requests (emails etc.):
Stored for as long as necessary to process your request and to comply with applicable legal obligations (e.g. statutory retention periods), and then deleted or anonymised.

2.7. Security

We take reasonable technical and organisational measures to protect the data we process (for example, protecting our email accounts with strong authentication).

However, no method of transmission or storage is completely secure. You are responsible for keeping your device and login information secure.

2.8. Changes to this Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time, for example if we:

introduce new features,

integrate advertising or analytics services, or

are required to do so by law.

The latest version will always be available at the URL where this document is published. The “Last updated” date at the top indicates the most recent revision.

3. Terms and Conditions
3.1. Scope and acceptance of the Terms

These Terms and Conditions (“Terms”) govern your use of the mobile game Mystic Quizmaster.

By installing, accessing or playing the Game, you:

confirm that you have read and understood these Terms, and

agree to be legally bound by them.

If you do not agree with these Terms, you must not install or play the Game.

3.2. No real prizes – entertainment only

Mystic Quizmaster is an entertainment game only.

All points, “souls”, cards, levels, ranks, achievements and other in-game items are purely virtual.

They have no real-world monetary value, cannot be exchanged for money, prizes, goods or services, and cannot be transferred or sold to other persons.

The Game does not provide any real-money winnings, payouts, or prizes of financial value.

The Game does not constitute gambling, betting or a lottery.

Any references in the Game to “millions”, “souls”, “rewards” etc. are purely symbolic and are part of the game’s fictional horror/fantasy theme.

