3.6. In-game content, horror theme and health

Mystic Quizmaster uses a fantasy horror theme with fictional ghosts, demons and other supernatural elements. All such content is fictional and intended for entertainment only. It does not represent real occult practices.

Some players may find the content disturbing. If you feel uncomfortable or experience negative effects, you should stop playing immediately.

To reduce eye strain or motion sickness, you should:

take regular breaks,

play in a well-lit environment,

stop playing if you feel dizziness, headache, nausea, or similar symptoms.

If you have a history of photosensitive epilepsy or other medical conditions that may be triggered by flashing lights or visual effects, consult a doctor before playing and follow the doctor’s advice.

